53edc7c7-3e42-4f9c-9895-82d9fe12c890.132fbc98-0137-4c4c-a1ea-6ee511cb82ea.description=Attempts to acquire the specified lock, and sleeps until the lock is available. 
Inputs\:
   uniqueLockId 	    - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.
   numberOfIteration 	    - specify how many times flow should try to acquire the the lock, if lock is not avaiable.
   numberOfSecondsToSleep  - The number of seconds to sleep for between each attempt at acquiring the lock.

Responses\:
   success - if the lock has been successfully acquired.
   failure - if the lock could not be acquired.

Result\:
   FailureMessage - returns failure details.

Notes\:
1) The locks acquired by this operation are not reentrant. This means that 
   once a lock is acquired by a run, all subsequent attempts at acquiring 
   the same lock by the same run (or any other run) will fail.

2) Once a run terminates, all the locks that were acquired during its execution
   are automatically released.
